rComments: Very good lectures, I would recommend her class to anyone interested in the sciences even if biology/anthropology isn't your thing.

Dr. Silcox's personality and sense of humour honestly make lectures worthwhile. Although anthropology isn't my major, she communicated course material in a way that made it very interesting and easy to follow. Be sure to do the readings (relate it back to lecture notes), attend lectures/labs and do not chat in the back... then you'll be fine.

Took C16 and A01 with her and I think she's an amazing teacher. She's hilarious and does an excellent job explaining everything. Her lecture slides don't have too much detail on them so attendance is important to do well. She makes it very clear what she expects of you for every test/assignment/exam and is fair. Did really well in both classes

Not the best professor. She teaches really fast paced. Used a really harsh TA who never came to lectures-- to grade our papers. Her lecture slides are very vague you need to sit in the front row and try your best to comprehend the material and pay attention. Lectures can be very boring.

Though she is strict and she has a very dry sense of humor which can be interpreted as grouchy or mean, Prof. Silcox is my favorite professor. Her lectures and assignments are very clear, removing a secondary level of stress from any paper or exam. I always do particularly well in her classes and try to take every class she offers.
Great professor, awesome sense of humour (her sarcasm flies over most peoples heads...). Would take again, even though anthro is not my major. Sometimes lectures can drag on a bit.

Very blunt and sarcastic sense of humour that flies above so many people's heads. Very sharp... hilarious. This is how anthropology should be taught! It really opened my eyes to how amazing the subject is. Incredibly easy too.
Awesome!

Dr. Silcox rocks! There r few profs who can make the bones and teeth of 60 million years old fossils seem sexy; shes one of them.  Completely knowledgeable and informative about the stuff she teaches.  She also bakes the yummiest skeleton and monkey cookies for dept  functions.
Explains things clearly, but you do need to put quite a bit of effort in order to get a good mark...

She is kind of mean, BUT she knows how to teach and that's all that matters since it helps you learn for the exam. Not really approachable, very strict. But slides are extremely organized and clear to follow.

She's how any other lecturer should be. The course was the highlight of my semester - She thoroughly knows what she's talking about, the lecture slides have everything you need to know to survive the class(she only lectures you on what she thinks you need to know. So you won't waste your time on other things). But NOT a bird course, needs work.
GOD HELP YOU IF YOU ARE LATE.Good prof. She is funny and the exam is lecture based.
Great professor. Fair marker, and very clear on material and expectations.

Amazing professor. Best experience so far at University. Lectures are extremely interesting, and she's super smart and a great person. Really cares about students and wants you to do well. Loved the class, and I would take pretty much anything that she teaches.

Super wicked prof, although she acts like a bit of a hard ass she's really SUPER funny and nice :) Almost every class I'd have a new little tid bit to tell my friends for example, "did you know there are full grown elephants the size of a great dane (extinct now of course)"
She's a great teacher.
She's a great teacher, and is real hot to boot!  Woo!

She's one of those profs that make you do well in class because she expects good work out of you, and you'll do anything not to disappoint her.  She's a bear, but a friendly one as long as you try hard and ask intelligent questions.

Although the lectures were good and she increased the interest of the subject matter, she was an angry person! Stalked around and looked pissed off all the time. Not very approachable outside of class.
Intelligent and very, very funny. Fabulous prof who makes everything interesting.
One of my favourite profs ever. Lectures are some times a little dull but the bulk is very interesting! Very kind and makes time for students!
Awesome prof, funny and very smart, though she can be pretty scary at times. You will definitely benefit from doing as she says.
Very good prof. Gives great notes and fair tests but hard marker on papers.  Relatively funny and easygoing but god help you if you are late!
impossibly hard on marking papers.  tends to dislike students who average below C+/B.
Excellent prof who knows her stuff.. just DON'T be late!!! She's funny and very interesting. If you follow her guidelines you'll do well.
ridiculous subject. silcox is ok.
Great. Interesting lectures. Helpful. Funny. Adorable. Dont be late. Dont talk in lecture. Relatively easy tests.
A great sense of humour!  Fun classes!  Just be sure to follow her essay guidelines and use proper taxonomy, or be ready to face the consequences!
No Comments
Great prof
Great teacher. Inspiring.
